# [LSR](../wg/lsr.html)

## Summary

The Link State Routing (LSR) Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss active working group documents, new proposals, and protocol enhancements for IS-IS and OSPF. The session covered a diverse set of topics, including routing protocol status, power-aware routing, replay protection, flooding reduction, active measurement autoprovisioning, microburst monitoring, distributed congestion mitigation, SRv6 egress protection, fragmentation synchronization, and process isolation. Key next steps include progressing several drafts on the mailing list and coordinating with other working groups (such as TEAS, RTGWG, and the Green WG).

