### 2. Using IS-IS to Advertise Power Groups
* **Presenter:** Ron Bonica
* **Slides:** [02-Using IS-IS to Advertise Power Groups](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-lsr-using-is-is-to-advertise-power-groups-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * **Summary:** The presentation highlighted the Power Conserving Path Placement Strategy (PCPPS). During periods of low traffic demand, CSPF calculations use a power-aware metric to consolidate traffic onto fewer links, allowing idle hardware to power down.
  * **Recent Updates:** 
    * Refined the model to focus on "power savings potential" rather than assuming powered-down states consume zero power. Credit was given to Carlos Pignataro for this enhancement.
    * Removed direct power group hierarchy definitions from this draft, instead referencing the abstract model in the TEAS PCPPS draft. Credit was given to Les Ginsberg for this separation.
  * **Questions and Comments:**
    * **Peter Psenak** asked if there had been consideration of using IGP Flexible Algorithms (Flex-Algo) with this proposal. Ron Bonica noted this was an interesting concept to explore.
    * **Acee Lindem** questioned whether this should remain Standards Track or become Experimental, referencing discussions with the Green Working Group. Ron Bonica noted they compared their proposal with the Green WG information model and found no contradictions.
    * **Chris Hopps** stated that working group adoption must occur before early IANA code point allocations can be authorized, but supported coordinating with Green WG without blocking progress.
    * **Zafar Ali** expressed concern regarding the accuracy of modeling power states across different vendors, suggesting that the foundational modeling work in TEAS must be adopted and stabilized before LSR proceeds with the routing protocol mechanics.
    * **Tony Lee** added that extensive discussions with the Green WG revealed no conflicts or reason to demote the document to Experimental, and recommended keeping it on the Standards Track.
  * **Poll:** A show-of-hands poll was conducted to gauge objections to working group adoption. Several participants objected. Zafar Ali reiterated his objection based on the dependency on the TEAS draft. The chairs decided to take the adoption call to the mailing list.

