### 5. IGP Active Measurement Group
* **Presenter:** Acee Lindem
* **Slides:** [05 - IGP Active Measurement Group](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-lsr-igp-active-measurement-group-01)
* **Discussion:**
  * **Summary:** This proposal introduces an automated mechanism to configure active measurement sessions (e.g., STAMP or TWAMP) across clusters of IGP routers, similar to how Seamless BFD (S-BFD) sessions are established.
  * **Recent Updates:**
    * Replaced the protocol bitmask with a single active measurement protocol ID per sub-TLV.
    * Introduced an 8-bit Group ID (with suggestions to expand this to 16 bits) to identify unique measurement paths or data-plane variations (such as SR vs. native IP).
  * **Questions and Comments:**
    * **Rakesh Gandhi** noted that since STAMP lacks the native control-plane signaling found in TWAMP (RFC 5357), obtaining stable responder parameters is difficult. He indicated Cisco is working on similar extensions and proposed aligning their efforts.
    * **Acee Lindem** agreed to take this offline to find common ground with the Cisco team and other contributors.

