### 8. SRv6 Mirror SID IGP Encoding
* **Presenter:** Tao
* **Slides:** [08-srv6-mirror-sid-igp-encoding](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-lsr-8-srv6-mirror-sid-igp-encoding-02)
* **Discussion:**
  * **Summary:** This draft defines the IS-IS and OSPFv3 encodings for the SRv6 Egress Protection framework developed in the RTGWG. It enables a protector node to advertise its relationship to a primary egress node using a Mirror SID (End.M behavior 74) and the associated protected locators.
  * **Questions and Comments:**
    * **Acee Lindem** noted that the authors successfully addressed previous feedback from the chairs regarding the reuse of existing sub-TLVs to simplify the encoding. He voiced support for moving the draft toward working group adoption to align with the core RTGWG document.

