### 9. Originator Sequence Number Checksum (OSNC)
* **Presenter:** Shraddha Hegde
* **Slides:** [09-hegde-lsr-isis-osnc-00](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-lsr-draft-hegde-lsr-isis-osnc-00-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * **Summary:** Addresses routing instability (such as transient route flaps or next-hop changes) that occurs when information is shifted across LSP fragments during asynchronous flooding.
  * **Technical Details:**
    * Originators include a new OSNC TLV carrying a 64-bit SipHash calculated over the LSP IDs, sequence numbers, and sizes of all self-generated fragments.
    * Receiving nodes verify the checksum. If a mismatch is detected (indicating some updated fragments have not yet arrived), the receiver can delay SPF calculations or BGP-LS updates up to a configurable timer.
  * **Questions and Comments:**
    * **Shraddha Hegde** acknowledged list feedback from Les Ginsberg. She explained that if a receiver receives a fragment with an updated checksum before the corresponding modified fragments arrive, the checksum will fail to match. To resolve this, the authors plan to introduce a global transaction ID in the next revision.
    * **Acee Lindem** commended the productive discussion occurring on the mailing list for this draft.

